question: Summarize the genus distribution in the antiSMASH dataset.
label: Test
answer_sql_expected: SELECT   t.genus,   COUNT(*) as genus_count FROM   antismash.genomes g   JOIN antismash.taxa t ON g.tax_id = t.tax_id GROUP BY t.genus;
answer_sql_LLM:
SELECT tax.genus, COUNT(*) as genus_count
FROM antismash.taxa as tax
JOIN antismash.genomes as gen ON tax.tax_id = gen.tax_id
GROUP BY tax.genus;

question: Which regions has iterative modules?

question: Which PKS regions has trans_at modules?

question: Find all NRPS regions with both glycosyltransferase halogenase SMCOGs
label: Test
answer_sql_expected: SELECT   g.assembly_id,   r.accession,   r.region_number,   smcogs.*,   smcog_hits.*,   cds.* FROM   antismash.regions r   JOIN antismash.dna_sequences d ON r.accession = d.accession   JOIN antismash.genomes g ON d.genome_id = g.genome_id   JOIN antismash.cdss cds ON r.region_id = cds.region_id   JOIN antismash.smcog_hits smcog_hits ON cds.cds_id = smcog_hits.cds_id   JOIN antismash.smcogs smcogs ON smcog_hits.smcog_id = smcogs.smcog_id WHERE   smcogs.description ILIKE '%glycosyl%'   OR smcogs.description ILIKE '%halogenase%';
answer_sql_LLM:
SELECT DISTINCT r.*
FROM antismash.smcog_hits sh
JOIN antismash.smcogs s ON sh.smcog_id = s.smcog_id
JOIN antismash.cdss c ON sh.cds_id = c.cds_id
JOIN antismash.regions r ON c.region_id = r.region_id
WHERE s.description ILIKE '%glycosyltransferase%'
AND s.description ILIKE '%halogenase%';
answer_summary_LLM: The data contains information on NRPS regions that have both glycosyltransferase and halogenase SMCOGs.

question: List all PKS regions in genome NBC_01737.

answer_sql_LLM:
SELECT r.*, bt.*, g.*, rt.*  
FROM antismash.regions r  
JOIN antismash.dna_sequences d ON r.accession = d.accession  
JOIN antismash.genomes g ON d.genome_id = g.genome_id  
JOIN antismash.rel_regions_types rt ON r.region_id = rt.region_id  
JOIN antismash.bgc_types bt ON rt.bgc_type_id = bt.bgc_type_id  
WHERE g.assembly_id = 'NBC_01737'

question: Find all NRPS regions with both glycosyltransferase halogenase SMCOGs
label: Test
answer_sql_expected: SELECT   g.assembly_id,   r.accession,   r.region_number,   smcogs.*,   smcog_hits.*,   cds.* FROM   antismash.regions r   JOIN antismash.dna_sequences d ON r.accession = d.accession   JOIN antismash.genomes g ON d.genome_id = g.genome_id   JOIN antismash.cdss cds ON r.region_id = cds.region_id   JOIN antismash.smcog_hits smcog_hits ON cds.cds_id = smcog_hits.cds_id   JOIN antismash.smcogs smcogs ON smcog_hits.smcog_id = smcogs.smcog_id WHERE   smcogs.description ILIKE '%glycosyl%'   OR smcogs.description ILIKE '%halogenase%';

SELECT DISTINCT r.*
FROM antismash.regions r
JOIN antismash.cdss cds ON r.region_id = cds.region_id
JOIN antismash.smcog_hits sh1 ON cds.cds_id = sh1.cds_id
JOIN antismash.smcogs s1 ON sh1.smcog_id = s1.smcog_id
JOIN antismash.smcog_hits sh2 ON cds.cds_id = sh2.cds_id
